snippet.textDisplay:
I could not be more enamored with Dave. That he has been so brilliant and so lucky to be surrounded by talent and love and respect from those countless in the audience and even more absent or long gone. No comedian of this age is as deserving of such an honor. George Carlin had the same exact energy and brilliance and compassion and shit-talking capability in order to be the tender person underneath; the 'Lion so you can be the lamb you are.' This made me swell and cry with true joy and pride. I am also easy to make cry, and do not apologize or feel humiliated about it because of this man. Knowing there is a man like Dave out there speaking volumes and using a medium that resonates with people is a comfort unparalleled. We all want to laugh, and we all want to be concerned and he can weave those two essential human elements seamlessly. Before you know he's done making a stinging or acerbic joke he's also planted a seed in your mind about something we observe but hadn't yet through the lens only he has been able and generous enough to allow us to borrow for a time.

Dave Chappelle, you are truly the measure of a success. Success as a human being, able to help us swell and cry and laugh until we BLEED, and for that we are so blessed. We will not live in your shadow, despite your inimitable brilliance. We will continue to be absolutely honored and while reverent, ultimately inspired to do our level best to contribute to one another.

To commit to ourselves and one another to make a truly amazing and incredible memory as you have admonished us to do so. Thank you for reminding us, we are all of us easy to forget such an effortless and necessary endeavor.

To be courageous enough to be yourself.

As Leonard Cohen wrote "Every thing has cracks in it, that's how the light gets in."


October 27th is my birthday, and Dave Chappelle day. I couldn't think of a better gift than to honor such a truly wonderful and beautiful human being.

Here's to you; an American hero and an American griot.
No pictures tonight, just memories.



And Dave, eat your fuckin vegetables and keep going.


We love you out here, like our own blood.

snippet.textDisplay: For a long time I have admired and loved him as a comedian and as human being.When I had nobody , I had him . Watched probably every video of him on youtube , every interview , podcast and stand up . Rewatched so many of them just because his voice , his intelligence ,eloquence , comedy and his character have become home . I watched him talk about his childhood and how much I saw  me in him . Maybe sounds cliche and pretentious because he is DAVE CHAPPELLE . I saw this on work for the first time and struggled to keep my cool . Came home and played this again and just watching him honor his mother and the way he described stand-up comedy and how much it means to him , I started crying like a baby , bawling my eyes out . One day I will get out of this place and move to states to chase that dream of becoming a stand-up comedian because he inspired me to do comedy for so many liberating reasons . LONG LIVE CHAPPELLE !
